main event: Two star-shaped, bright white objects were sighted in the sky over Alexandria, Louisiana on September 7, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were the size of a pencil eraser held at arm's length.
One object was visible for 2 minutes and the other for 3 minutes.
The objects flew in a straight line, one from west to east and the other from south to north.
Weather balloons launched from nearby areas may have contributed to the sighting.
The observers were deemed competent and sincere, and several aircraft were also spotted in the area that evening.
